


1.  ehci-msm Driver.   Qualcomm modem driver thing.
                       Manually install into kernel tree (see below)

    Makefile:
    Kconfig:
    ehci-msm.c:      <root-kernel-src>/drivers/usb/host

    msm_hsusb_hw.h:  <root-kernel-src>/include/linux/usb


2.  The defconfig

    defconfig:       <root-kernel-src>/arch/arm64/configs


3.  Get kernel, and Kernel build instructions

    1.  reference instructions from:  https://boundarydevices.com/wiki/linux-kernel-imx8/

    2.  Install build tools (only once on your machine)

        sudo apt-get install crossbuild-essential-arm64

    3.  imx8 Kernel comes from:

        git clone https://source.codeaurora.org/external/imx/linux-imx

    4.  Use this branch:

        git checkout imx_4.19.35_1.1.0

    5.  Manually add in the ehci-msm driver from above

    6.  Makes the config, the Image, the Modules, and the Device Tree Binary

        export ARCH=arm64
        export CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-linux-gnu-
        make defconfig
        make Image modules dtbs -j8






